<style>
div {
  font-size: 20px;
  color: transparent;
}

div:nth-of-type(1) { background: green; }
div:nth-of-type(2) { background: blue; }
div:nth-of-type(1),
div:nth-of-type(2) {
  height: 5ch;
  width: 5ch;
}
div:nth-of-type(1) { background: green; }
div:nth-of-type(2) { background: blue; }
div:nth-of-type(1),
div:nth-of-type(2) {
  height: 5ch;
  width: 5ch;
}
div:nth-of-type(3) {
  background: orange;
  writing-mode: vertical-rl;
  text-orientation: upright;
  height: 5ch;
  width: 5ch;
}
</style>
<body>
  <p>Test passes if there is a <div></div> one, not the orange one.
  <p>If any of the 3 colored shapes is not a square, or if the orange one.
  <p>If any of the 3 colored shapes is not a square, or if the orange and blue squares are the same size, the test fails.
